There is a custom of high antiquity still retained in Wales, which is not very different from this of Greece and Arabia3 but which, in point of inno- cence and picturesque effect, is far more commend- able: I mean that of collecting and strewing roses, and other odoriferous flowers, at the annual village wake of sheep-shearing, antecedently to the banquet which is afterwards liberally provided for the artless and honest swains.
